-l      latest (replacement for container id. applies command to the latest used container in any Podman command)
-t      --tty, pseudo-terminal is allocated for the container and attaches to standard input of the container
-i      --interactive, keeps standard input open, even if detached, so the main process can continue waiting for input
-d      --detach, container runs in the background detached
-p      --publish, used for port forwarding
-h      --hostname, sets container host name that is available inside container
-can    reads commands from string
-e      --env, set up environment variables


